<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07835</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING THE MUNICIPAL AGRICULTURE INFORMATION SYSTEM</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to provide for the computerization and integration into a unified Agricultural Commodity Supply Inventory/Registry System of all information in the agricultural supply-demand chain; Provides that this centralized database under the Department of Agriculture shall interconnect farmers and organized communities all over the country with an easy-to-access data on real-time market demand, both local and global, for agricultural commodities, thus creating a wider range of market linkages to both farmers and agricultural buyers.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “ Municipal Agriculture Information System Act ( M A I S Act) ”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ALEJANO, GARY C.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-05-31</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON AGRICULTURE AND FOOD ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>